{{Quote|My mother, my aunts, my uncles, the cousins I've lost&hellip;they're all there. Their faces, their voices&hellip; I don't have any other way to remember them. And I'm not alone. So many on Melida/Daan have nothing to remember their loved ones by except the Halls of Evidence.|[[Cerasi]]|<ref name="Jedi Apprentice: The Uncertain Path">''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Uncertain Path]]''</ref>}}
The '''Halls of Evidence''' were memorial halls set up on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Melida/Daan/Legends|Melida/Daan]]. A combination of war shrine and [[Burial/Legends|mausoleum]], the halls contained homages to the members of the [[Melida/Legends|Melida]] and [[Daan (people)/Legends|Daan]] populations who were killed during the civil war on Melida/Daan. Most contained [[Hologram/Legends|holograms]] of dead persons, who left a holographic memory and propaganda speech that served to incite further violence between the two groups, in a cycle of endless warfare and hate.

A faction known as [[the Young]], made up of the younger generation on both sides, eventually rose to power, overthrowing the Elders. Led by [[Nield]], his government formed a new history squad that began to tear down the Halls of Evidence, and many of the Halls were destroyed because they were thought to inspire hate. However, this action itself precipitated another bout of violence when the Elders and Nield's followers, both armed, converged on the halls. [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Cerasi]], a former leader of the Young, arrived to try and prevent the violence, but Cerasi, who was unarmed, was shot and killed.

